details.description:
Provided Coffee Concord is a mega-cafe located next to Nothing New Vintage, behind Southern Strain Brewing. We are proud to be one of the largest coffee shops in NC! We serve an assortment of handcrafted espresso beverages and bottled drinks.

Founded by two best friends at 18 years old, Provided aims to create an atmosphere of community wherever travelled. As coffee can act as a bridge of connection between others, the customer can expect "special experiences in unusual places."

raw_data.description:
Provided Coffee Concord is a mega-cafe located next to Nothing New Vintage, behind Southern Strain Brewing. We are proud to be one of the largest coffee shops in NC! We serve an assortment of handcrafted espresso beverages and bottled drinks.

Founded by two best friends at 18 years old, Provided aims to create an atmosphere of community wherever travelled. As coffee can act as a bridge of connection between others, the customer can expect "special experiences in unusual places."
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 2.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text:
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
“Absolutely loved my visit to Provided Coffee! Sam was amazing—she made beautiful designs on both my lattes and was so sweet. Her warmth and attention to detail truly made my day. Highly recommend this place for great coffee and even better service!”

The Orange Dreamsicle Latte was so delicious. The multiple different spots to sit were so cozy and welcoming. The atmosphere of the entire place was laid back and fun. I was able to just sit and crochet and enjoy my coffee. I will definitely be back.

Super cute coffee shop with eclectic seating. Love the aesthetics and vibes of the cafe. I myself was sitting on a church pew during my stay. Good music and plenty of space to get work done. Also, the whole reason you’d stop by… the coffee. This stop I didn’t get any coffee but the blackberry matcha and chai were fantastic. The chocolate chip cookie was also the perfect amount of crumbly and had salt on top to give it that extra flavor.

I spent the day with my son who is home from college. I had visited Southern Strain Brewing & Eatery around a month ago & loved it!
In that review I had made a brief mention of this coffee shop.

While exploring today, we met the owners (Cohen & Preston) & they were really nice.

They made us seasonal coffee called orange Creamsicle and my son really loved it!

They also  have another Provided Coffee location in Uptown that we’ll need to try the next time we’re in that part of Charlotte.

You will love this unique coffee space with its vintage furniture and decor & what’s awesome is it’s conveniently located in this old mill that houses both a brewery with food and a vintage shopping experience.

Happy Exploring 🧭

Josephine Local Guide
The cappuccinos and lattes are consistently excellent, never burnt or overly roasted. Perfect every time.
10/10, no notes.

reviews_data.review_text: Concord’s pride and joy!
What a cool place!!

I moved to Concord about five months ago and was looking for a local coffee shop. I tried a couple different ones and then I found provided coffee which was right around the corner from where I am located. And out of the three coffee shops that I tried, they were the best! Now I go there every morning!
Always a 10/10 experience. Delicious drinks.
Cool little coffee shop inside Nothing New clothes store

This place felt like finding hidden treasure!
This cafe certainly isn’t lacking for space so forget not being able to find a spot! Akin to shopping for your optimal seating preference… window seat, a cozy place on the sofa, a chair with a table, perhaps? Absolutely sit down and stay for a while! Their seasonal menu also lands on top with delightful options such as orange creamsicle and blackberry. This coffee shop captures great service with an inviting ambiance and happy tastebuds to match. Bonus points for having a vintage clothing store in the same building! Lastly, the music choice was superb.

one of my favorite places to visit. i really enjoy trying their seasonal drinks and i love how much seating is available! i would also say that they have a pretty cool collection of clothes, but my favorite part of the shop is the plant section. staff is also very kind!

Great coffee house. Very vibey in a “nobody understands me” sort of way. It has a brewery and a thrift shop attached that are also really cool. Coffee was amazing and they really take their time making it.
Hands down the best coffee and atmosphere in Concord! I love coming here to work and bringing my daughter on the weekends. Highly recommend!

First time here - it’s a little confusing to find the entrance but worth it.  Got an iced carmel latte and it was very good!  Probably best local coffee I’ve had.  I am visiting this area and don’t know if it’s sketchy or not normally, but I did have a creepy man in a cowboy hat follow me to my car and made me spill half of my drink trying to get away from him.  I barely was able to get in my car and lock the door before he was right in front of my window.  Just be aware of your surroundings but this is a really cool spot and the staff was great too!!
This is my go to place for some alone book and coffee time. I love coming to this place and have a cup of seasonal coffee.
This place is really good and comfortable.

The staff and decor are, in my opinion a extremely enjoyable, comfortable and cozy atmosphere.  The coffee quality is high, and the The owners, staff and family of are awesome, down to earth people. It would be difficult to not come back.

Friendliest coffee place in town. Plenty of space to plug in and fellowship. These folks meticulously roast their own beans so prepare for a unique but pleasing experience, unlike the chain coffee shops.
It takes a minute to find the entrance, but don’t give up. It’ll be worth it when you arrive.
And if you’re in the market for the cute kid with all the hair, sorry but he is quite happy with his soon to be bride. but no worries. He will treat you as kind and warm as always!

I love Provided for a lot of reasons outside the amazing coffee. One of them is how kind ALL the staff are. They always speak and genuinely seem like they enjoy what they do. Cohen and Preston are both awesome owners who know how important customer service is. I can’t wait to work with them for our wedding (they also cater with a super cute coffee cart) MUCH LOVE

10/10 experience every time. Staff is very efficient and attentive. The atmosphere is amazing and the coffee is some of if not the best in Cab co. Couldn’t recommend enough!

Give them a follow on instagram, I promise it’s worth it ;)
real good coffee, real friendly, and real cozy to do work or hang out in!
I’m on a mission to try a new coffee shop once a week, and I absolutely loved Provided Coffee! Plenty of space to study or just enjoy conversation with others. I will definitely be coming back!

Everything here is perfect. The atmosphere, the staff, the choice and quality of drinks made. I wish I could give 20 stars for this place. I will definitely be making this a very frequent stop for myself, and you should too!

Some of the best/unique artisanal flavors in the NC Piedmont region when it comes to coffe shop drinks. Friendly and courteous staff with a location to match. Enjoy spending time reading and studying. Honored to have them as a neighbor here in Concord.
You won't find a better latte around. The homemade sauces, and fun seasonal menus are on point, and every single employee is friendly and competent. We visit on a weekly basis!
Always enjoy my time at this coffee shop. All the baristas are wonderful and the coffee is my favorite (and I’ve tried all the local shops)
Excelente 👌
Authentic, balanced espresso drinks. Perfect milk foam. It’s also very affordable - I spent around $8 for a cortado and a cappuccino. If you care about authentic espresso, this is the place to go.
This is my favorite coffee shop. The staff is great and it is such a relaxed environment.  Easy to sit and enjoy conversation or do some work. I love their coffee selections.
High quality coffee, interesting flavors (coffee cake! 😋) a lovely, knowledgeable staff, and a beautiful, cozy ambiance. I will definitely be back!
One of the best coffees in Concord and amazing vintage shop with an atmosphere usually only found in bigger towns.
Just what a coffee shop needs to be. Friendly, personal, and great coffee

Impatient, once I played 2 keys on the piano over at display and someone came immediately to put a note saying do not touch it. I felt it was a little rude and the person could have spoken to me about that. I felt embarrassed.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey! Thanks for your feedback, no matter what we are sorry that you felt embarrassed at our shop.. we are assuming this experience was a few weeks ago, as we’ve had a ‘please do not play’ and a keys cover over the piano for a few weeks.. our goal is to make a welcoming and good atmosphere for everyone present and keeping the piano display unplayed is a piece of that. We know you wished someone would have spoken to you, but we prefer our barista’s to maintain the shop and not directly confront customers unless absolutely necessary.. for their own safety. We never know who comes through our doors and we never want to subject our staff to a confrontation with a stranger especially while management is not present. We would love for you to come back and have a better experience- so next time you come to either location, show this response to our barista and we will get you a free drink on us. Have a great day!

reviews_data.review_text: Cohen and his team at Provided are so personable and make the best coffee drinks. I come here sometimes to work and get out of the rut of remote working and have a nice place to sit and work. I came in this morning not sure what to order and Cohen made me the most delicious caramel latte. Love it here! Also it's so cool that an 18 year old started this business and now has TWO locations! That's so impressive.
Hands down the best coffee shop around. Great atmosphere, plenty of space to work, friendly staff, and of course, the best coffee. 10/10 recommend.
This is the best coffee shop in town never seen anything like it. Go get you some dang good coffee.
Some of my favorite coffee in let alone Concord! Staff are awesome and being within Nothing New is a super plus!
Wonderful visit and chill atmosphere
Love, love, love the coffee and the artistic ways of each coffee's presentations! The atmosphere is a super comfortable experience and very spacious!!
The toilets seem to be always very nasty… pretty big deterrent especially when you can smell the bathroom from outside them.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
hey! Thank you for your review, we want you to know we've taken huge steps and made improvements to maintain all restrooms daily, We'd love for you to come back and try us again, show this to the barista working to get a free drink on us! 

We are a small business and are always trying to improve, we hope when you return you see that!
Cheers.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is super cozy. It is a combination of a coffee shop and a vintage clothing store.  I love all the vintage furniture in the loft style setting. I love the warehouse space it is in. The Orange latte that I had was even the orange flavor was too subtle for me. But everyone was friendly. Great place to work on the computer. You can play chess or just relax. Really cute space.

Cool space to hang out with friends. If you need a change of scenery it's a great place to study or work remotely.
Delicious espresso and the staff is friendly

This is honestly a one star review, but since I didn’t try the product, I’m leaving 3 stars. Trying to be “fair” and not offset the reviews that speak to how great the coffee tastes.

I frequent coffee shops all over NC. I tend to ask a lot of questions since each shop has its on thing going for them—and also to be more informed about services and options.

I was quite polite, but it seemed like my questions were making the barista annoyed. I was going to opt for a matcha when he informed me they couldn’t do half-caf lattes, but his overall demeanor and the way he handle me genuinely hurt my feelings. I drove over 40 mins to check this place out, but left a bit heartbroken and without ordering anything.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey! Thank you so much for your review, we take all experiences very seriously and want to make sure we serve our community well. We would love to look back at this interaction, what was the specific time & day you went? 

We are committed to excellence & care- Thank you for also giving us 3 stars although you would rate your experience lower.. if you do choose to return, show this reply to a barista working and get a free coffee on us.

reviews_data.review_text:
Creamy, delicate cappuccino in an atmosphere which truly blew my mind. The massive brick building is shared with a brewery and vintage shop. There is plenty of space to work, shop and play.

I have to say, this Cappuccino ranks in my top three all-time. Beautiful presentation, exquisite taste.

Dude! This place is awesome. Recently moved here from Denver and haven’t found good coffee until we stumbled upon this shop. I always get a cortado to test the espresso and it was solid; not a super complex flavor but very smooth and balanced. You can tell they really care about their craft here, plus the space was very inviting. New favorite on the map.
Great place to chill out and have some coffee

This place was recommended to us. It was a bit confusing getting to the place but we finally found it. This coffee shop is inside a vintage clothing store! (Who knew!?)
The place is huge and they have a ton of comfy seating nooks and corners with lots of plant’s. Very cool! The coffee was pretty good, the flavor of the espresso was more on the fruity side but wasn’t super strong so the milk in my capp was a bit overpowering. They only serve their coffee in Togo cups, a bit of bummer. We will be back to try some other drinks next time!
One p☝️ This

Super cute understated place - coffee was amazing and the barista was super nice! Fun little vintage shop but what I really loved was the PLANT SECTION !?!? 🤩🤩🤩🥲 amazing !! gorgeous !! so aesthetically pleasing 😌 They also had fun varieties of exotic plant seeds
So aesthetic place . I got a matcha latte :)

Coffee drinks were very well made. Service was prompt and courteous. Atmosphere was well thought out and comfortable. The only thing missing was a food option, something like a local bakery would be perfect.
Best coffee in concord! Cool space, too

I don't drink coffee, but when I need a beverage that is provided, I have a chocolate milk.  Preston is a wizard with his beverages, and Cohen is a master at ambiance.  I have to say, these guys make a MEAN chocolate milk.  Will be back!

Provided is one of the most exciting businesses to open in the area in such a long time. Their carrot cake iced latte is to die for. I’ve never had to complain about an order. Nothing New adds so much to the atmosphere but even when it’s closed, Provided’s section is very very relaxing.
One of my favorite coffee shops to stop at, all employees are super friendly and welcoming
Great vibes. Good place to grab a cup and work with some friends or creative juices flowing
Coffee and lattes were excellent, but small.
I think it’s a great place to come and work or just hang out for a while. It’s such a cool place.
This place is incredible and exactly what I was looking for to get some work done. So spacious, yet still has cozy vibes. The people there were also really nice. I will definitely be back!
Loved the staff. Coffee was great and got Alot of work done there too. Amazing space 😄
Everything about provided is great coffee and the people are top notch! Highly recommend!
No notes 😙🤌
The atmosphere is nice, but the actual coffee and chai is not as good as other local coffee shops in the area (Press and Porter, Allegiance Coffee, Defined Coffee, etc.).

It’s a cool place with beautiful decor… however the location isn’t the most obvious. Coffee was really nice, but the let down was that they only have oat milk as a milk alternative. Would love to see more options for milk ☺️
This place has everything: good coffee, tons of seating, reliable wifi, and ✨vibes✨It is definitively the best coffee shop in Concord and you should go!
I love to introduce clients to Provided! The atmosphere is amazing, the coffee delicious and the people watching second to none. 👀
Best coffee in concord! Best baristas, best vibe, best experience

Definitely a coffee shop worth going to everyday!  haven’t been to this location yet, but honestly giving it a 5 star now cause of how well they’ve made the uptown location so cozy and welcoming. Coffee is always great & the latte art never disappoints. The first time i walked in & got a coffee from Preston he made me feel like i was a good friend from years back, you don’t find that from most coffee shops these days. This location seems like it’s about to knock my socks off. With all that being said i am going tomorrow & will most likely stand firm on my 5 star review.
Always have a good experience and the coffee is GOOD
Now our favorite coffee spot!  Tons of creative space and the coffee is top notch!
I loved the open space design. We met friends here and enjoyed having our own living room space together. The coffee was good; we had wished for a breakfast menu.
We ordered the Carrot Cake Oakmilk  latte and Iced Oatmilk latte. The atmosphere was calming and we spent hours there. The young man at the Cash point was absolutely amazing!!! Thank you.

Man if you haven’t met the two legends who are behind this incredible coffee shop…you need too! Cohen and Preston are two of the most genuine and hardworking guys you’ll ever meet and their coffee proves it🤟🏽 Love you guys!

I’m the definition of coffee snob and I love this place and it’s coffee.

If you are a fellow snob privy to Charlotte’s local coffee shops like Not Just Coffee, Undercurrent and Night Swim…I would say these guys are keeping up with them!

It is hands down the best in concord.

The Honey Latte with cinnamon is my go-to!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Taylor! Thank you so much for the kind words , we hope you do come back soon! When you come please enjoy 15% off your next order :) just show this to the barista when you are at the counter.

reviews_data.review_text: Didn't go here. Google maps was insufficient, said it was half as far away! Small signs with arrows outside building weren't either. I walked into a brewery early that morning!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey John, we are sorry to hear this experience. We are located at the end of the driveway, when you turn into the brewery… but you can also walk through the brewery to our space , it is the glass door next to the bar. Unfortunately we cannot speak for Google maps as we have no control over how it directs. We have an A-frame sign at the entrance to the parking lot leading to our front door and 2 green signs with arrows pointing to our door at the end of the parking lot. We also have a video on our instagram of how to get inside.. you may need to scroll down on our reels section to find it. We are a very small business & do not take any reviews whether good or bad lightly. We would like to welcome you back to get a free coffee from us & revisit this review after your experience. Show our staff this response and they will make sure your drink is free. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Hated coffee for almost two decades. Provided is one of the key reasons I love it now. Provided Concord has a fantastic atmosphere and space, with incredible coffee and roasting expertise, and awesome staff. 5 stars all the way.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey! I was quite polite, but it seemed like my questions were making the barista annoyed. I was going to opt for a matcha when he informed me they couldn’t do half-caf lattes, but his overall demeanor and the way he handle me genuinely hurt my feelings. I drove over 40 mins to check this place out, but left a bit heartbroken and without ordering anything.
